post_text:
SCHOOLOGY - How to sign-on?

Hello Plainfield Public School Parents and Students,
So, How does a student log into Schoology? They use his/her district google account. To watch videos on how to log in, please visit the district website main page. If you need additional help, please email a school vanguard listed on the district main page or email schoologysupport@plainfield.k12.nj.us

Schoology - como entrar a la sesion?

Hola, padres y estudiantes del Distrito Escolar de Plainfield:
Entonces, ¿cómo ingresa un estudiante a Schoology? Usan la cuenta de Google de su distrito. Para ver videos sobre cómo iniciar la sesión, visite la página principal del sitio web del distrito. Si necesita ayuda adicional, envíe un correo electrónico a la vanguardia escolar que aparece en la página principal del distrito o envíe un correo electrónico a schoologysupport@plainfield.k12.nj.us

Plainfield Public Schools' Preschool Program has openings for all-day Pre-k for the New 2020-2021 School Year. Parents must pre-register online and after completing the first two steps, they will receive a phone call to complete the pre-registration application. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact the Office of Early Childhood Divina Guzman or Phyllis Doddy at (908) 731-4200 Ext. 5354 or Ext. 5359

Queridos todos,
El Preescolar de las escuelas públicas de Plainfield tiene vacantes para el prekínder de todo el día para el nuevo año escolar 2020-2021. Los padres deben pre-inscribirse en línea y después de completar los dos primeros pasos, recibirán una llamada telefónica para completar la solicitud de preinscripción. Si tiene alguna pregunta o inquietud, comuníquese con la Oficina de Primera Infancia Divina Guzman o Phyllis Doddy al (908) 731-4200 Ext. 5354 o Ext. 5359

post_text:
COOK SCHOOL KINDERGARTEN ORIENTATION
Principal: Dr. Caryn Cooper

Plainfield Supt. of Schools Dr. Mitchell joined Cook School Kindergarten Orientation! She welcomed the C/O 2039! Conducted in Eng/Span tonight by Principal Dr. Caryn Cooper and Staff & Teachers.

La Dra. Mitchell, Superintendente de Escuelas, se unió a la sesión de orientación de los padres de niños en kindergarten. La Dra. dio la bienvenida a la clase del 2039! Conducidas en Inglés/Español por la Dra. Caryn Cooper, Directora de la escuela Cook, las maestras y empleados.

Items discussed
1. Schoology
2. I Ready Math
3. How Cook School Communicates - importance of attendance and letting the school know if the child is going to out.
4. Lunch applications

Los temas de discussion incluyeron:
1. Schoology
2. I ready Math - matemáticas
3. Como se comunica la escuela con los padres y la importancia de comunican a la escuela si el niño va a faltar
4. Como solicitar para almuerzo reducido o gratis

ADVISORY - Plainfield Public Schools Buildings will be closed today - Employees are to work remotely.
In light of the Governor's announcement regarding the statewide "State of Emergency for Hurricane Isaias," Plainfield Public Schools Buildings will be CLOSED today, August 4, 2020. All 12-month employees will work from home. Please do not drive on the roads. Employees are not to report to the buildings. Please be safe!

AVISO - debido a Huracán Isaias los edificios del distrito escolar estaran cerrados hoy.
Debido a la declaración de Emergencia del gobernador debido al huracán Isaias - todos los edificios del distrito estarán cerrados hoy, 4 de Agosto 2020. Todos los empleados trabajaran desde sus casas. Por favor no maneje hoy, quédese en casa. Mantengansen seguros!

post_text:
PLAINFIELD PUBLIC SCHOOLS - JUNETEENTH PROJECT
Source: Jared McClain (Visionary) and Najiyyah Bailey (PHS) Class of 2001
Juneteenth marks the end of slavery in Texas on June 19, 1865 two years after the Emancipation Declaration was declared by President Abraham Lincoln January 1, 1863. The slaves in Texas were the last to find out and on this day they called it Juneteenth. On June 19, 1865, Union General Gordon Granger led thousands of federal troops to Galveston, Texas to announce that the Civil War had ended, and slaves had been freed. (Source: US.gov)

https://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?flash=false&doc=40

Projecto de Juneteenth (Celebrando el final de la esclavitud) es la fecha en que los esclavos en Tejas se enteraron que habian sido liberados dos años después que el Presidente Abraham Lincoln aprobó la Declaración de Emancipación. El 19 de Junio de 1865 el General Gordon Granger apoyado del batallón de tropas federales fue a Galveston, TX para anunciar que la Guerra Civil había terminado y que los esclavos habian sido liberados. (crédito: varios del Us.gov)

A Message from Brooke Vuono, Director

Un mensaje de la directora del centro de cuidados para ninos de la escuela superior Plainfield High School.

“Congratulations to our graduating teen parents- Class of 2020!
Evelyn Alvarado, Nairobi Avila, Dominic Chipantiza, Keily Hasbun, Meylin Lopez, John Perez, Olga Ramirez, Lesli Tista and Stephanny Torres!

You have all worked so hard and are incredibly dedicated to your children. We never cease to be impressed by your accomplishments and how you have turned challenging circumstances into a bright future.
Good Luck ! We will miss you!

Uds. han trabajo fuerte y con gran dedicacion a sus ninos. Nosotros siempre estamos sorprendidos por sus logros y de la forma que han cambiando una circumstancia dificil en una luz para su futuro.
Buena Suerte! Los extranaremos.

Courtesy: Jackasha Wiley, Director, Rutgers University Upward Bound Program, Pre-College Initiatives Division of Diversity and Community Engagement and PHS Alumni.

Congratulations to Plainfield Public Schools Alumni who graduated from Rutgers University and Barry University in 2020! We are so proud!!

Alumni Ugonna Amaechi C/O 2015 just completed her Bachelor’s degree in Human Resource Management and Africana Studies from Rutgers University-School of Arts & Sciences.

Alumni Kamar Kellam C/O 2016 just completed her Bachelor’s of Science degree from Delaware State University and will be attending Barry University for graduate school.

Alumni Sidney Ramirez C/O 2016 just completed her Bachelor’s degree in Animal Science from Rutgers University-School of Environmental & Biological Sciences.

PLAINFIELD PUBLIC SCHOOLS - PLAINFIELD HIGH SCHOOL Class of 2020 - A group of students from Plainfield High School (PHS) were honored today by their church and Principal Dion Roach. Rev. Victor Aloyo, Jr. invited Mr. Roach, Actor Producer Lin-Manuel Miranda and others to offer words of inspiration to the students. Among the graduates were: Vanessa Mazariegos, who will be attending Raritan College, Yerik Amaya, who will be entering PHS, and Dunis Franco, Jr. who plans to study mechanical automation.

El Director de la escuela Plainfield High School Dion Roach se unio al Rev. Victor Aloyo, Jr. y otros para ofrecer su apoyo a graduandos del distrito escolar de Plainfield.

PLAINFIELD PUBLIC SCHOOLS - EVERGREEN SCHOOL
A Virtual Training Session was held May 28, 2020 with over 82 Parents, Teachers, and Administrators who participated. Congratulations to the winners of the two baskets that were raffled between all the participating parents! The training was guided by Mr. Stibich and translation was provided by Mr. Cevallos to assist parents in accessing Google Classroom and reviewing the postings from teachers, and fun activities to engage the children in.

La sesion incluyo como utilizar la plataforma de instruccion y como abrir las instrucciones de las maestras (os) y como utilizar actividades divertidas para entretener a los niños.

Credits: Ms. Vianey Castillo, Teacher, Ms. Gina Ogburn-Tompson, VP, Ms. Jeraldine Salazar, Secretary.

(Moscow would join one day later.) Traffic in Cape Town came to a stop. That night, Scotland lit up for the first time since the war began.
Source: NYPost

PLAINFIELD PUBLIC SCHOOLS STUDENTS & FAMILIES
A Message from Dr. Diana Mitchell, Superintendent of Schools

HAPPY NURSES APPRECIATION DAY! ❤️

Good Morning to our Champion Nurses in Plainfield Public Schools!

Happy Nurses Appreciation Day! For all your kind words, band-aids, peppermints, taking our temperatures, and especially those magical bags of ice – we say THANK YOU for serving the students and families of Plainfield.

It really takes a special kind of nurse to work in schools, not only take care of children, but also take care of the teachers, administrators, and other staff members. You are the true heart ❤️ of healthcare! Enjoy your day of recognition.

EMERSON SCHOOL - POP ART by
Ms. Santiago’s students in Grades 3-4

The students art is inspired by the artist Andy Warhol. They copied his style of pop art to create self portraits in various colors to promote awareness to be safe during this pandemic. They used an app called comic life for filters a combined them in another app called sketchbook.

#popart #AndyWarhol #sketchbook #RemoteLearning #StudentArt

El arte de los estudiantes está inspirado po el artista Andy Warhol. Copiaron su estilo de arte pop para crear autorretratos en varios colores para promover consciencia en la seguridad durante esta pandemia. Utilizaron una aplicación llamada comic life y sus filtros y los combinaron con otra aplicación llamada sketchbook.

post_text:
All New Jersey school buildings will remain closed for in-person instruction for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year and all students and faculty will continue with remote-learning.
Private schools with longer academic years will remain closed until at least June 30.

https://nj.gov/governor/news/news/562020/docs/A3813AV.pdf

This difficult decision was made based on the guidance from public health experts with a single goal in mind, the safety and well-being of our children and our educators.
If the standards to reopen our workplaces are high, they are even higher when it comes to schools filled with our children. The State simply could not find a way to reconcile that core principle and open our school buildings at this time.
The hurdles -- logistical, educational, and, most of all, practical -- that would have allowed students and faculty to return, even for a short while, could not be overcome. We could not guarantee an environment that would not only be safe, but fully cap

PLAINFIELD PUBLIC SCHOOLS STUDENTS & FAMILIES
Report Cards Message from:
Mr. Mark A. Williams, Assistant Superintendent

Plainfield Public Schools report cards for the 3rd marking period were mailed out Friday, May 1, 2020. All report cards will be available via the parent portal as well. Only the schools that receive paper-based report cards during the school year will receive them now. Those schools who view their report cards via the parent portal only, will continue that practice. Thank you.

Las calificaciones del tercer periodo fueron enviadas por correo a los estudiantes de las Escuelas Públicas de Plainfield el viernes 1 de mayo de 2020. Todas las calificaciones también estarán disponibles a través del portal para padres en el internet. Solo las escuelas que reciben las calificaciones en papel durante el año escolar las recibirán ahora tambien en papel. Las escuelas que solo tienen acceso a las calificaciones a través del portal para padres continuarán esa práctica. Gracias.

#TeamPPSD. #Championsforstudents #RemoteLearning
